    2063 MATMOD Matrix modification Main Index Option P1 = 17 Generate a g -size partitioning vector from a user -defined set of grid and/or scalar points or from a degree-of- freedom set or combination of sets in the USET table. Format: Form 1: (SIL is specified and NROW is unspecified) Form 2: (SIL is specified and NROW is specified) Form 3: (BGPDT is specified and SIL or NROW are both unspecified) Input Data Blocks: Output Data Block:MATMOD EQEXIN,USET,SIL,CASECC,GRIDLIST ,EDT/CP/17/ UBIT/SETFLG/S,N,NOCP////UWM6968//// SETSTR1/SETSTR2/SETSTR3/SETSTR4 $ MATMOD EQEXIN,USET,,CASECC,GRIDLIST ,EDT/CP/17/ UBIT/SETFLG/S,N,NOCP///NROW/UWM6968//// SETSTR1/SETSTR2/SETSTR3/SETSTR4 $ MATMOD BGPDT,USET,,CASECC,GRIDLIST ,EDT/CP/17/ UBIT/SETFLG/S,N,NOCP////UWM6968//// SETSTR1/SETSTR2/SETSTR3/SETSTR4 $ EQEXIN Equivalence table between external and internal grid/scalar identification numbers. BGPDT Basic grid point definition table. USET Degree-of-freedom set membership table for g-set. SIL Scalar index list. CASECC Table of Case Control command images. GRIDLIST List of grids. Single record table in this format: <grid 1><grid 2>… List may be unsorted and contain duplicates. EDT Table of SET1 entries. See SETFLG parameter. CP Column partitioning vector.

    MSC Nastran DMAP Programmer’s Guide Matrix modification2064 Main Index Parameters: UBIT Input-integer-default=0. Obsolete method for set selection. For a more user-friendly method use SETSTRi. In order to select specific sets for UBIT , add the corresponding decimal equivalent numbers from the table below. For example, sets R, O, and MP , UBIT=8+4+1=13. For supersets, add the decimal equivalent numbers of the mutually exclusive sets which are contained in the superset. For example, set S combines the SB and SG set and therefore UBIT=1024+512=1536. The presence of any grid point degree of freedom in the associated sets causes all degrees of freedom associated with that grid point to be given a value of 1.0 in the output vector. Set NameDecimal Equivalent Number Q 4194304 LM 2097152 C 1048576 J 524288 K 262144 SA 131072 E 2048 SB 1024 SG 512 MR 16 R 8 O 4 B 2 MP 1

    2065 MATMOD Matrix modification Main Index Remarks: 1.EQEXIN or BGPDT may not be purged. 2.CASECC may be purged if SETFLG=0 or GRIDLIST is specified. 3.SIL may be purged if NROW or BGPDT is specified or SETFLG=0. 4.BGPDTD, EQDYN, USETD, SILD, and LUSETD are generated from the DPD module and may specified in place of BGPDT, EQEXIN, USET, SIL and LUSET if extra points are present. Example s: 1.Generate a partitioning vector from a set of grid points requested by the PARTN Case Control command; e.g., SET 10 = 1 THRU 50 PARTN = 1 0SETFLG Input -integer -default=0. If SETFLG  0, then SETFLG selects a set of grid point identification numbers of which all degrees of freedom associated with each point will be assigned a value of 1.0 in the corresponding row of CP . If no SET command is found, then the SETSTRi or UBIT parameter is used. SETFLG<0: If EDT is not present then absolute value of SETFLG selects the SET Case Control command. If EDT is present then absolute value of SETFLG selects the SET1 Bulk Data entry. SETFLG=0: See SETSTRi or UBIT . SETFLG>0: PARTN=SID Case Control command selects the SET
    command or uses GRIDLIST. If GRIDLIST is present then PARTN command is ignored. NOCP Output-integer. NOCP will be set to -1 if the partitioning vector is null or cannot be generated. Otherwise, it will be set to zero. NROW Input-integer-default=0. Number of rows in CP when SETFLG<>0 and SIL is purged. Usually this is the LUSET or LUSETD parameter . See Remark 4. UWM6968 Input-integer-default=0. UWM 6968 print control flag. = 0: Print ≠ 0: Do not print SETSTRi Input-character-default=’ ‘. Set name string. SETSTR1 through SETSTR4 form a single string of set name(s) and is 32 characters in length. The set names must be separated by a plus sign, “+”. For example, SETSTR1=‘M+R+N+SG’ and SETSTR2=’+A+Q’ specifies the m, r, n, sg, a, and q sets. SETSTRi specification takes precedence over UBIT specification.

    2069 MATMOD Matrix modification Main Index Format for Sparse Factor Matrix (FORM=13): Format for Active Column Factor Matrix (FORM=4): Input Data Block: Output Data Blocks: Remarks: 1.Sparse symmetric decomposition forms the equivalent matrix representation of a symmetric matrix. where P is a permutation matrix (row and column interchange used to improve efficiency), L, a lower triangular matrix, and D, a tridiagonal matrix.     2077 MATMOD Matrix modification Main Index Option P1 = 33 Create a single column matrix from the frequency response output list table, (FOL), load factor list table (OLB) or transient response time list table (TOL). Format: Input Data Block: Output Data Block: Parameters: Option P1 = 34 Extract the real and imaginary parts of complex matrix into two real matrices. Format: Input Data Block: Output Data Blocks: Option P1 = 35 Sorts row term values in a selected column of the input matrix and produces a list vector and/or a Boolean matrix that contains the indices of the sorted terms.MATMOD FOL,,,,,/FOLMAT,/33/P2/P3 $ FOL Output list of frequencies, load factors, or times. FOLMAT Matrix of frequencies (FOL), load factor list table (OLB) or transient response time list table (TOL). P2 Input-integer-default=0. By default, the first two words which represent the name of the table are skipped. P2=1 directs the program not to skip the first two words. P3 Input-integer-default=0. By default, the table is assumed to be a list of frequencies which will be converted to radians in FOLMAT . P3=1 directs the program not to convert to the radians. The Boolean square matrix contains unit values in the appropriate positions so that it can be used to create the sorted input matrix by means of a simple matrix multiply as in: producing the sorted IM matrix, IMS, as Remarks: 1.If the matrix input into this option contains more than one column and SORTBOOL is used subsequently to operate on this matrix, all columns will have their rows re-ordered according to the sort obtained from the column processed by the MATMOD operation. A test on a typical vector showed a difference of a factor of approximately ten. If repeatability is not essential, NKEYS=1 is the preferred choice.
